14/11/2008
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Lawmakers on Thursday (November 13th) appointed a committee to supervise the activity of the National Security Agency.
The panel will consist of six members -- three from the ruling coalition of the Bulgarian Socialist Party (BSP), the Movement for Rights and Freedoms and the National Movement for Surge and Stability and three from the opposition.
Nadka Baleva of the BSP became chairwoman of the committee, which has two weeks to hammer out its own procedural regulations and submit them to parliament for approval.
(News.bg, Standart, Netinfo, Dnevnik - 13/11/08)
